 *  Krishna Muralidhara — Devotional Animation  v3.1  (stutter-fixed)
 *  ESP32 · SSD1306 128×64 portrait-mounted · Adafruit_SSD1306
 * ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
 *
 *  BUG-FIX LOG  (v3.0 → v3.1)
 *  ────────────────────────────
 *  BUG 1 — Vertical jumping (PRIMARY stutter cause)
 *    Cause: breatheY used (int) truncation on a [-0.8, +0.8] value.
 *           C truncates toward zero, so (int)(-0.7f) = 0, not -1.
 *           subpixelDither then toggled the whole figure ±1 px every frame
 *           → 25 Hz vertical strobe visible to the eye.
 *    Fix:   Removed breathe Y entirely. A 0.8 px vertical oscillation is
 *           imperceptible on OLED — it only manufactured noise.
 *
 *  BUG 2 — Horizontal shimmer / edge noise (SECONDARY stutter cause)
 *    Cause: subpixelDither() toggled per-column pixels at 25 Hz.
 *           On a 1-bit OLED this is full-brightness flicker, not smoothing.
 *           "Sub-pixel dithering" is a concept for LCD subpixels; it does
 *           not apply to monochrome OLEDs.
 *    Fix:   Removed subpixelDither entirely. Integer rounding via
 *           lroundf() gives cleaner steps than frame-alternating dither.
 *
 *  BUG 3 — Feather tip jumping independently
 *    Cause: Separate integer feather offset snapped between 0/±1
 *           on its own phase, creating a visible independent twitch.
 *    Fix:   Feather sway is now blended into body leverage continuously
 *           (weighted additive float) — single lroundf() at the end.
 *           No separate integer step.
 *
 *  WHAT REMAINS FROM v3.0
 *  ────────────────────────
 *  ✓ Delta-time animation (frame-rate independent)
 *  ✓ Phase wrapping (no float drift)
 *  ✓ DT cap (guards against I²C stalls)
 *  ✓ sinf() pre-computed once per frame
 *  ✓ Wire.setClock(400000) for max FPS
 *  ✓ setRotation(1) portrait mode
 *  ✓ 50 FPS spin-wait with micros()
 *  ✓ 1.7× bitmap (39×107 px, LANCZOS + sharpened)
 *
 *  WIRING
 *  ───────
 *  SDA → GPIO 21   SCL → GPIO 22   VCC → 3.3V   GND → GND
 */

